title: Could Liberals be wiped out in the SA election? | ABC NEWS
description: ABC Chief Elections analyst Casey Briggs says incumbent Labor Premier Peter Malinauskas won’t be sweating the result of the SA election. The more interesting question is, just how big will Labor's win be? title: OpenAI researcher speaks on why she resigned | ABC NEWS
description: Wall Street lost $1 trillion this month as investors reacted to the rapid growth of AI and fears about its impact on jobs. title: South Australian election countdown officially begins, campaign kicks off | ABC NEWS
description: The election countdown has officially begun in South Australia, with both major parties seizing the opportunity to start making their formal pitches to voters on the first day of the campaign.  Election proceedings were triggered after the writs were issued at Government House on Saturday by Lieutenant Governor Richard Harris.  The formality brought South Australia's 55th Parliament to an end, placing the state government into caretaker mode and marking the start of the 28-day campaign. title: US Supreme Court rules Trump's global tariffs illegal | ABC NEWS
description: US President Donald Trump has lashed out at members of the Supreme Court who struck down his global tariffs after finding he had no authority to implement them.  The decision means the US may be forced to pay back more than $US100 million in tariffs already collected.  Mr Trump has vowed to find other ways to implement tariffs, using laws unrelated to the court decision. He said he would issue an order for a 10% global tariff later in the day.
